10/02/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The opposition Croatian People's Party (HNS) announced Wednesday (9 February) that it has submitted a voter registration bill, aimed at preventing fraud, to parliament.
According to HNS parliament member Zeljko Kurtov, the party is proposing the establishment of a special state body that would be responsible for co-ordinating voter lists.
At the same time, the existing State Election Commission would monitor the county registries and control the registration of expatriate voters.
(index.hr - 09/02/05)
